A year after the Copenhagen Agreement, it is time to consider compliance with the promises of early and fast-start funding by developed countries.
And the big French craps are revealed.
In the Copenhagen Agreement, developed countries committed themselves to providing $30 billion between 2010 and 2012.
The European Union has promised €7.2 billion over three years and France €1.26 billion (i.e. 420 million per year).
At the opening of the COP16, the EU released the big game to convince its partners of the reality of its commitment to fast start financing: report detailing the action of its Member States, press conference, large side event, distribution of brochures...
