First of all, France could announce a change in its accounting mode for 2011 and 2012, in a spirit of respect for its commitments and fairness with the other countries of the European Union.
But above all, France could make discussions on the issues of long-term financing progress (other crucial chapter currently discussed): the question of "additionality" or the method of accounting for loans will not be avoided.
